    <tags>javascript typescript runtime sandbox security cli developer-tools</tags>
    <summary>Secure-by-default JavaScript and TypeScript runtime.</summary>
    <description>
3va is a secure-by-default JavaScript and TypeScript runtime built on QuickJS with post-quantum cryptography and capability-based sandboxing.

Key properties:
- Deny-by-default permission model — filesystem, network, env, and subprocess access must be explicitly granted per script
- Post-install scripts blocked unconditionally — 3va never executes arbitrary code at package install time
- No pm2 or process manager required — built-in process supervision
- Post-quantum TLS (ML-KEM / ML-DSA) and WASM support included
- MIT licensed

Install with: choco install 3va
Run: 3va --help
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/OdinoCano/3va/releases/tag/vv2.1.3</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
